Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_default_switching_activity(25.10)    get_default_switching_activity(25.10)

Name
       get_default_switching_activity

Syntax
       get_default_switching_activity

       [-help]

       [-clip_activity_to_domain_freq]

       [-clock_gates_enable]

       [-clock_gates_output]

       [-clock_gates_output_ratio]

       [-comb_clockgate_ratio]

       [-duty]

       [-global_activity]

        [-icg_ratio]

       [-input_activity]

       [-macro_activity]

       [-period]

       [-seq_activity]

       Displays the following information about a set_default_switching_activ-
       ity parameter in the system log file and in the system console:

              * Parameter name

              * Current value

       If  you  do  not specify a parameter, the software displays information
       for all of the set_default_switching_activity parameters.  The  get_de-
       fault_switching_activity  command  prints only the user-specified value
       for the parameters. If a parameter has not been set using  the  set_de-
       fault_switching_activity  command,  the  get_default_switching_activity
       command does not output any information in the console.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each get_default_switching_activity parameter. For
              a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters,
              use the man command: man set_default_switching_activity.

       <parameter_names>
              Displays information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify one or more parameters.

              See  set_default_switching_activity for description of the para-
              meters you can specify.

Examples
       The following command displays the current setting of the -period para-
       meter:

       get_default_switching_activity -period

       The software displays the following information:

       -period {20}

